4. `tests/test_resolve_openalex.py` ã see Test. Use `respx` to mock HTTP.

## Test (TDD red step)

```python
# tests/test_resolve_openalex.py
import respx
from httpx import Response
from maiba.config import load_config
from maiba.model import Item
from maiba.resolvers.openalex import OpenAlexResolver

CFG = load_config("config/maiba.yaml")

@respx.mock
def test_resolve_by_doi_returns_full_record():
    respx.get("https://api.openalex.org/works/doi:10.1016/j.egypro.2009.02.302").mock(
        return_value=Response(200, json={
            "id": "https://openalex.org/W123",
            "doi": "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.egypro.2009.02.302",
            "title": "Engaging the public on CCS: a large group process",
            "publication_year": 2009,
            "authorships": [
                {"author": {"display_name": "Peta Ashworth"}},
                {"author": {"display_name": "Simone Carr-Cornish"}},
            ],
            "host_venue": {"display_name": "Energy Procedia"},
        })
    )
    resolver = OpenAlexResolver(CFG)
    item = Item(TY="JOUR", TI="Engaging the public on CCS",
                AU=["Ashworth, P.", "et al."], PY=2009,
                DO="10.1016/j.egypro.2009.02.302")
    result = resolver.resolve(item)
    assert result is not None
    assert result.candidate.JO == "Energy Procedia"
    assert "Carr-Cornish" in " ".join(result.candidate.AU)
    assert result.source == "openalex"
    assert 0.0 <= result.confidence <= 1.0
```

## Exit criteria

- `make test` green; `respx` mocks every HTTP call (no real network in tests).
- All thresholds and endpoints come from `Config`.
- Smoke run on one DOI from `ArchiveCCS.ris` returns plausible candidate
  (manual eyeball, not asserted).
